# Commit title format:
# type(scope): short summary
#
# Optional breaking format:
# type(scope)!: short summary
#
# Allowed types:
# feat, fix, perf, refactor, docs, style, chore, build, ci, test
#
# Allowed scopes:
# api, admin, launcher, platform, desktop, shared, core, ui, release
#
# Rules:
# - use lowercase type and scope
# - keep summary concise and imperative
# - do not end the summary with a period
#
# If breaking:
# BREAKING CHANGE: <what changed and migration guidance>
#
# If multiple meaningful changes are included in one commit body, use lines like:
# * feat(api): ...
# * fix(shared): ...
#
# Examples:
# fix(launcher): show app version in compact header
# ci(platform): update semantic release workflow inputs

